@AkihiroSuda because of [this](https://github.com/containers/podman/pull/10704#discussion_r653631161) and [this](https://github.com/containers/podman/issues/10297#issuecomment-925869282)

As @mheon mentioned, the proposed PR does not cover all cases, and slirp4netns change will be initially limited to rootless mode. I imagined an average DevOps person blindly setting `networksetup` hook from a random guide on the web and being sure he "protected" the network. Rather than document several caveats in the documentation, why not do it right in scope?

Maybe I am missing something here?
